    Scope and Contents
Keldermans, a native of Belgium and carillonneur for the Thomas Rees Memoiral Carillon in Springfield's Washington Park, discusses his musical education in Europe; a carillon's construction, casting bells, sound quality and maintenance; playing styles and techniques; composing; effects of WWII on the carillons of Europe; history of the instrument; Thomas Rees, Springfield's carillon, and the yearly festival; and master carillonneurs. 1 tape, 38 mins., 25 pp. 
Interview by John Bucari, 1975 
OPEN 
See collateral file: interviewer's notes, photos, program of the inaugural Carillon Festival at Concordia Seminary in St. Louis, and brochures about carillons.  
  
